description:
&lt;p&gt;** This is a Substantive and Fixed Term / Secondment opportunity (until 6th June 2021)**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you interested in working in a challenging environment?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are a busy maternity unit looking for positive, enthusiastic and motivated people to join our Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our maternity service provides care for approximately 5,500 deliveries per year. We have 7 teams providing community based midwifery services. Our in-patient facilities consist of 32 postnatal beds including 5 transitional care beds, and 13 antenatal beds. The Delivery Suite has 15 birthing rooms including a birthing pool, 2 obstetric theatres, anaesthetic and recovery room, providing a full range of facilities for high dependency care. Plus the Maternity Assessment Unit, which is based on Delivery Suite and aims to provide a service to those requiring day attendance and review. We have a co-located Midwifery Led Birthing Unit which comprises of four birthing rooms with waterbirth facilities available. We have a commitment to provide one-to-one care to all women in established labour, and are very proud to have achieved and maintained full BFI accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous midwifery care assistant experience is an advantage. Candidates must be willing to work towards NVQ Level 3 development in the future. Progression towards Band 3 Senior Midwifery care assistant positions is possible via a supported college framework in the future for appropriate candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under the direction of the Registered Midwife work with all members of the multi-disciplinary team, to provide the highest standards of patient care within maternity services. The Midwifery Care Assistant may be required to assist in any clinical area within the Maternity Department in response to Service demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will involve supporting midwives in the delivery of care to mothers, babies and their families. Duties will include checking physical wellbeing with blood pressure and urinalysis measurements, new born feeding support, accurate recording and reporting of information and administrative support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to undertaking general ward routines, you will participate in audit/data collection as required and be competent with the electronic patient systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See Job description for more details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is rotational throughout the Maternity Services, and will involve shift working covering the service 24 hours a day, every day of the year. Shifts comprise of Long days 07.00-19.30 hours and nights 19.00-07.30 hours in most areas, with some variations of this in others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work flexibly in accordance with shift patterns and rotation throughout the maternity service, covering both days and nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shifts are also available to assist in our busy Antenatal Clinic which runs during the usual working week mainly 8-6 or similar variants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum working hours are 24 per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who have previously been interviewed and found unsuccessful, need not apply please.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** If you are considering applying for this post on a secondment basis, please discuss with your Line Manager prior to applying to ascertain whether this could be supported **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;** full and part time hours available **&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 3rd December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 5th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barbara Jackson - Antenatal Clinic &amp; Post Natal Services Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: &lt;/strong&gt;01603 286796&lt;/p&gt;
